#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.41:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 5. Sagāthakapuññābhisandavagga → asaṅkheyyasuttaṃ (bj) | abhisanda 1 or sayhaka 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.41:0.2"
msgid "5. Sagāthakapuññābhisandavagga "
msgstr "5. Overflowing Merit, With Verses "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 41. Paṭhamaabhisandasutta → sagāthapuññābhisandavaggo (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.41:0.3"
msgid "41. Paṭhamaabhisandasutta "
msgstr "41. Overflowing Merit (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn55.41:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puññābhisandā, kusalābhisandā, sukhassāhārā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurture happiness. "

msgctxt "sn55.41:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn55.41:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.41:1.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.41:1.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn55.41:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.41:2.2"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …. "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.400, sc3
msgctxt "sn55.41:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr "Furthermore, they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion. … "

msgctxt "sn55.41:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.41:3.3"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puññābhisandā, kusalābhisandā, sukhassāhārā. "
msgstr "These are the four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurture happiness. "

# NOTE: Note that in parallel passages AN uses gahetum here.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn55.41:4.1"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi puññābhisandehi kusalābhisandehi samannāgatassa ariyasāvakassa na sukaraṃ puññassa pamāṇaṃ gaṇetuṃ: "
msgstr "When a noble disciple has these four kinds of overflowing merit and goodness, it’s not easy to measure how much merit they have by saying that "

msgctxt "sn55.41:4.2"
msgid "‘ettako puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro’ti. "
msgstr "this is the extent of their overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurtures happiness. "

msgctxt "sn55.41:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of merit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn55.41:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde na sukaraṃ udakassa pamāṇaṃ gaṇetuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s like trying to measure how much water is in the ocean. It’s not easy to say "

msgctxt "sn55.41:5.2"
msgid "‘ettakāni udakāḷhakānī’ti vā ‘ettakāni udakāḷhakasatānī’ti vā ‘ettakāni udakāḷhakasahassānī’ti vā ‘ettakāni udakāḷhakasatasahassānī’ti vāti. "
msgstr "how many gallons, how many hundreds, thousands, hundreds of thousands of gallons there are. "

#. VAR: asaṅkhyeyyo → asaṅkheyyo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.41:5.3"
msgid "Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāudakakkhandhotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of water. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.41:5.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, imehi catūhi puññābhisandehi kusalābhisandehi samannāgatassa ariyasāvakassa na sukaraṃ puññassa pamāṇaṃ gaṇetuṃ: "
msgstr "In the same way, when a noble disciple has these four kinds of overflowing merit and goodness, it’s not easy to measure how much merit they have by saying that "

msgctxt "sn55.41:5.5"
msgid "‘ettako puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro’ti. "
msgstr "this is the extent of their overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurtures happiness. "

msgctxt "sn55.41:5.6"
msgid "Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti. "
msgstr "It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of merit.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn55.41:6.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn55.41:6.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn55.41:7.1"
msgid "“Mahodadhiṃ aparimitaṃ mahāsaraṃ, "
msgstr "“Hosts of people use the rivers, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:7.2"
msgid "Bahubheravaṃ ratanagaṇānamālayaṃ; "
msgstr "and though the rivers are many, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:7.3"
msgid "Najjo yathā naragaṇasaṅghasevitā, "
msgstr "all reach the great deep, the boundless ocean, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:7.4"
msgid "Puthū savantī upayanti sāgaraṃ. "
msgstr "the cruel sea that’s home to precious gems. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.1"
msgid "Evaṃ naraṃ annapānavatthadadaṃ, "
msgstr "So too, when a person gives food, drink, and clothes; "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: paccattharaṇassa → seyyānisajjattharaṇassa (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.2"
msgid "Seyyāni paccattharaṇassa dāyakaṃ; "
msgstr "and they’re a giver of beds, seats, and mats—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.3"
msgid "Puññassa dhārā upayanti paṇḍitaṃ, "
msgstr "the streams of merit reach that astute person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.4"
msgid "Najjo yathā vārivahāva sāgaran”ti. "
msgstr "as the rivers bring their waters to the sea.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

